===Etymology===
{{IPAchar|/ipu/}} → {{IPAchar|/iɸu/}} → {{IPAchar|/*iwu/}} → {{IPAchar|/iu/}} → {{IPAchar|/juː/}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|-}},<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref> from {{inh|ja|jpx-pro|*ipu}}. Possibly cognate with {{cog|ko|입|t=mouth}}.

Medial {{IPAchar|/h/}} regularly changed from {{IPAchar|[p]}} → {{IPAchar|[ɸ]}} → {{IPAchar|[w]}}. Japanese never distinguished between {{IPAchar|/wu/}} and {{IPAchar|/u/}}, so that automatically becomes {{IPAchar|[u]}}. The {{IPAchar|/w/}} only surfaces in the negative form of ''i'''w'''anai'', where the phoneme {{IPAchar|/wa/}} exists. Surface forms {{IPAchar|/iwimasu/}} and {{IPAchar|/iwemasu/}} automatically become {{IPAchar|/iimasu/}} and {{IPAchar|/iemasu/}} since Japanese no longer distinguished {{IPAchar|/wi, we/}} from {{IPAchar|/i, e/}} (although this distinction has [[re-emerge]]d in borrowed terms).

