====Usage notes====
As a transitive verb, this can take the usual [[accusative]] [[particle]] {{ja-r|を}} after the object of the verb.  However, it is much more common to see this with the [[quotative]] particle {{ja-r|と}} instead.

Compared to other verbs such as {{ja-r|喋る|しゃべる}}, {{ja-r|話す|はなす}} and {{ja-r|語る|かたる}}, which refer specifically to speaking, this verb is abstract, and sometimes used like a copula, as in {{ja-l|そういう}}, {{ja-l|ああいう}}, {{ja-l|こういう}}, {{ja-l|っていうこと}}.<ref>{{cite-book|2005||精選版 日本国語大辞典|trans-title=Selected edition: unabridged Japanese language dictionary|publisher=Shogakukan|lang=ja}}</ref>

====Idioms====
{{der-top|Idioms}}
* {{ja-r|言う 迄 も ない|いう まで も ない}}: it goes without saying
* {{ja-r|言う に 及ばず|いう に およばず}}: it goes without saying; it isn't easy to say {{qualifier|not reaching the point of being easily expressed}}
* {{ja-r|言う に 足らず|いう に たらず}}: it isn't worth bringing up; it isn't easy to say {{qualifier|not sufficiently clear, not easily expressible}}
* {{ja-r|言わん 方 無し|いわん かた なし}}: no way of saying it
* {{ja-r|言わぬ が 花|いわぬ が はな}}: “not saying it, is a flower” → it would be better to leave it [[unsaid]]
* {{ja-r|言わず も がな|いわず も がな}}: “not even saying would be preferable” {{qualifier|either because it is already known and doesn't need saying, or because not expressing it at all would be better}}
